Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: django-admin-ckeditor
Version: 0.0.1
Summary: Ckeditor integration with Django admin.
Home-page: https://github.com/madisona/django-admin-ckeditor
Author: Aaron Madison
Author-email: UNKNOWN
License: UNKNOWN
Description: Basically this is just the CKEditor javascript files with a 'fields.py'
        file providing a 'RichTextField' and a 'CkeditorWidget' that attaches
        the proper javascript to the form field widget.
        
        
        1. Declare a model with a 'RichTextField'.
        2. in the admin.py, use the formfield overrides to add the CKeditor widget
           to rich text fields.
        
        
        --- models.py ---
        from ckeditor.fields import RichTextField
        
        class SampleModel(models.Model):
            description = RichTextField()
        
        --- admin.py ---
        from ckeditor.fields import RichTextField, CkeditorWidget
        
        class SampleModelAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):
            formfield_overrides = {
                RichTextField: {'widget': CkeditorWidget},
            }
        
        
